3. Claiming credits and deductions one is not entitled to;
4. Using the stolen identities of others to apply for loans or credit cards; 
5. Transferring assets before reporting income in order to lower tax bills; and/or 6. Setting up false charitable organizations and using these as conduits through which to channel embezzled funds from illicit enterprises

