3. Mischaracterizing payments as expenses or revenue; or 
4. Creating duplicate purchases or billing schemes, causing duplicate payments from vendors etc. Once these vulnerabilities are identified, it is critical that they are reported immediately so that the proper steps can be taken to ensure secure finance operations before exploiting them for personal gains.

